claim.claim-text:
6. A structure for a field-effect transistor having a body and a gate, the structure comprising: 
an insulative saddle structure having a middle section contacting the gate, and having two opposing insulative sidewalls contacting the body; 
a conductive saddle structure having a middle section contacting the middle section of the insulative saddle structure, and having two opposing conductive sidewalls each contacting one of the opposing insulative sidewalls.

36. An integrated dynamic-random-access-memory circuit comprising: 
a plurality of memory cells; 
an address decoder coupled to the plurality of memory cells; 
first and second complementary field-effect transistors having respective first and second gates and bodies, with the first and second gates coupled to at least one of the memory cells; and 
first and second capacitances coupled respectively between the first gate and body and between the second gate and body.

38. A method of making a field-effect transistor, comprising: 
forming an NMOS or PMOS island on a semiconductive substrate, with each island having at least two opposing sidewalls and a gate region; 
forming an insulative layer between the NMOS or PMOS island and the semiconductive substrate; 
forming dielectric sidewalls on the two opposing sidewalls of the NMOS or PMOS device island; and 
forming conductive sidewalls on the dielectric sidewalls, with the conductive sidewall extending from the gate region of the NMOS or PMOS island to the insulatlive layer.

43. A method of making a field-effect transistor, comprising: 
forming an NMOS or PMOS island on a semiconductive substrate, with each island having at least two opposing sidewalls and a gate region; 
forming an insulative layer between the NMOS or PMOS island and the semiconductive substrate, wherein forming the insulative layer forms silicon nitride sidewalls on the device island; 
forming dielectric sidewalls on the two opposing sidewalls of the NMOS or PMOS device island, wherein forming the dielectric includes removing at least a portion of the silicon nitride sidewalls; and 
forming conductive sidewalls on the dielectric sidewalls, with the conductive sidewall extending from the gate region of the NMOS or PMOS island to the insulatlive layer.

48. A method of making a field-effect transistor, comprising: 
forming an NMOS or PMOS island on a semiconductive substrate, with each island having at least two opposing sidewalls, a gate region, and a layer with a retrograde dopant profile; 
forming an insulative layer between the NMOS or PMOS island and the semiconductive substrate, wherein forming the insulative layer forms silicon nitride sidewalls on the device island; 
forming dielectric sidewalls on the two opposing sidewalls of the NMOS or PMOS device island, wherein forming the dielectric includes removing at least a portion of the silicon nitride sidewalls; and 
forming conductive sidewalls on the dielectric sidewalls, with the conductive sidewall extending from the gate region of the NMOS or PMOS island to the insulatlive layer.

54. A method comprising: 
providing a semiconductive layer having a major surface; 
doping the semiconductive layer with a p-type dopant to define a first retrograde dopant profile in a dimension perpendicular to the major surface; 
forming an n-well in the semiconductive layer, with the n-well having a second retrograde dopant profile in the dimension perpendicular to the major surface; 
forming a first insulative layer over the n-well and a portion of the semiconductive layer adjacent to the n-well; 
forming a conductive layer over the first insulative layer, with the conductive layer having portions overlying the n-well and the portion of the semiconductive surface adjacent to the n-well; 
removing portions of the conductive layer, the first insulative layer, and semiconductive layer to defne at least first and second device islands, with each device island having at least two opposing sidewalls, a gate layer, a doped layer with a retrograde dopant profile, and a portion of the first insulative layer between the gate layer and the doped layer; 
electrically isolating the first and second device islands from the semiconductive layer; 
forming dielectric sidewalls on the two opposing sidewalls of each device island; and 
forming conductive sidewalls on the dielectric sidewalls of each device island, with each conductive sidewall extending at least from the gate layer of the device island to the doped layer with the retrograde dopant profile.

61. A method comprising: 
providing a semiconductive layer having a major surface; 
doping the semiconductive layer with a p-type dopant to define a first retrograde dopant profile in a dimension perpendicular to the major surface; 
forming an n-well in the semiconductive layer, with the n-well having a second retrograde dopant profile in the dimension perpendicular to the major surface; 
forming a first insulative layer over the n-well and a portion of the semiconductive layer adjacent to the n-well; 
forming a conductive layer over the first insulative layer, with the conductive layer having portions overlying the n-well and the portion of the semiconductive surface adjacent to the n-well; 
removing portions of the conductive layer, the first insulative layer, and semiconductive layer to defne at least first and second device islands, with each device island having at least two opposing sidewalls, a gate layer, a doped layer with a retrograde dopant profile, and a portion of the first insulative layer between the gate layer and the doped layer; 
electrically isolating the first and second device islands from the semiconductive layer, wherein electrically isolating the device islands includes forming silicon nitride sidewalls on the device islands; 
forming dielectric sidewalls on the two opposing sidewalls of each device island, wherein forming the dielectric includes removing at least a portion of the silicon nitride sidewalls on each device island; and 
forming conductive sidewalls on the dielectric sidewalls of each device island, with each conductive sidewall extending at least from the gate layer of the device island to the doped layer with the retrograde dopant profile.

68. A method comprising: 
providing a semiconductive layer having a major surface; 
doping the semiconductive layer with a p-type dopant to define a first retrograde dopant profile in a dimension perpendicular to the major surface; 
forming an n-well in the semiconductive layer, with the n-well having a second retrograde dopant profile in the dimension perpendicular to the major surface; 
forming a first insulative layer over the n-well and a portion of the semiconductive layer adjacent to the n-well; 
forming a conductive layer over the first insulative layer, with the conductive layer having portions overlying the n-well and the portion of the semiconductive surface adjacent to the n-well; 
forming a protective cap layer on the conductive layer, with the protective cap layer defining at least first and second perimeters; 
etching the conductive layer, the first insulative layer, and the semiconductive layer to define first and second device islands in accord with the first and second perimeters, with each device island having at least two opposing sidewalls, a gate layer, a doped layer with a retrograde dopant profile, and a portion of the first insulative layer between the gate layer and the doped layer, and with a portion of of the protective cap layer overlying the gate layer; 
forming a second insulative layer between the semiconductive layer and the first and second device islands; 
forming dielectric sidewalls on the two opposing sidewalls of each device island; and 
forming conductive sidewalls on the dielectric sidewalls of each device island, with each conductive sidewall extending at least from the gate layer of the device island to the doped layer with the retrograde dopant profile; 
removing the portion of the protective cap layer overlying each gate layer to define a recess between the opposing sidewalls of each device island; 
forming a conductive structure in the recess of each device island, with each conductive structure electrically coupling the conductive sidewalls of the device island; and 
doping first and second regions of the doped layer of each device island, with the first and second regions on respective sides of the gate layer of the device island.
